author: The Capital-Journal
title: Former Topeka High star Alec Beatty honored by Midwest Conference
text:
Former Topeka High star Alec Beatty honored by Midwest Conference Three-time All-City pick registers seven tackles, two interceptions in first collegiate start on defense Posted: October 19, 2015 - 5:06pm By The Capital-Journal 
ST. PAUL, Minn. — Former Topeka High standout Alec Beatty’s first defensive start in college proved a dandy. 
Beatty, a three-time All-City selection, recorded seven tackles and two interceptions, including one at the goal line, this past Saturday to help Macalester secure a 28-14 victory against Beloit. The outing earned Beatty honors as Midwest Conference defensive performer of the week, the league announced Monday. 
A freshman who started the season at quarterback, Beatty also recovered a fumble in the first quarter, rushed three times for 17 yards and had a 19-yard punt return for Macalester. Beatty’s performance led a defensive effort that yielded only 272 yards offense to Beloit, which entered the game averaging 499 yards. 
Beatty and the Scots will continue Midwest Conference play against Lawrence at 1 p.m. Saturday in Appleton, Wis.
